Tips:
    
    - You can run js methods in the browser console by typing its name followed by parenthesis
        E.g. helpfulTip() //Paste this in browser console

    - you can view a websites dataLayer by typing dataLayer in the console.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    

The Data Layer is a virtual space between a website and server.
The Data is normally used by marketers for tracking :)



Any key:object value can be stored.

object can be of any type ( string, int, boolean )

This is a really good article on the dataLayer

    https://umbraco.com/blog/a-developers-guide-to-the-data-layer/




****************************** ****************************** ******************************
IMPORTANT NOTE:
    ( Im not certain but better to be safe)
    Remember to clear you dataLayer after playing with this app as it may affect browser performance if you fill it 

    Option 1:
        navigate to dev tools Application
        if Local storage has many items in it as a list click on each one to find the local storage data named in this code
        Delete manually
    Option 2:
        if you have nothing worth keeping etc... GitHub password for auto login
        Then paste in console =>
        localStorage. clear()
